Let $X, Y, Z \in \powerset S$.
Then:

X \circ_\PP \paren {Y \circ_\PP Z} = \set {x \circ \paren {y \circ z}: x \in X, y \in Y, z \in Z}
\set {\paren {x \circ y} \circ z: x \in X, y \in Y, z \in Z}
\paren {X \circ_\PP Y} \circ_\PP Z

demonstrating that $\circ_\PP$ is associative on $\powerset S$.

